WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:56.680 --> 00:02:02.100
Captain Kuro of
a Thousand Plans

31
00:01:57.260 --> 00:01:58.350
What was that?!

32
00:01:58.350 --> 00:01:59.640
What did he do?!

33
00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:02.100
It looked like his arm stretched!

34
00:02:00.730 --> 00:02:02.100
Get real!

35
00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:05.650
He knocked Captain Kuro
flat on his ass!

36
00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:24.620
I leave the rest to you...

37
00:02:26.540 --> 00:02:28.460
so leave the treasure to me!

38
00:02:29.710 --> 00:02:34.930
– The Usopp Pirates have arrived!
– The Usopp Pirates have arrived!

39
00:02:35.590 --> 00:02:36.340
Guys!

40
00:02:36.340 --> 00:02:37.350
Stay back!

41
00:02:37.890 --> 00:02:39.510
Say your prayers, butt-ler!

42
00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:41.770
You had it coming!

43
00:02:42.180 --> 00:02:45.060
A dumb pirate like you
disturbing the peace...!

44
00:02:43.890 --> 00:02:45.810
S-Stop!

45
00:02:47.060 --> 00:02:50.110
What the hell do you brats
think you're doing?!

46
00:02:51.280 --> 00:02:53.110
What're those kids doing?!

47
00:02:53.110 --> 00:02:56.780
Stop that, you guys... Stop!

48
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:03.330
Alright! We'll let you off with just that!

49
00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:10.420
C-Captain Kuro has
gotta be fuming now!

50
00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:13.970
Captain, you came after all!

51
00:03:13.970 --> 00:03:15.720
You were fighting back for real!

52
00:03:15.720 --> 00:03:17.840
Why didn't you tell us?!

53
00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:19.220
We fell by the waste side!

54
00:03:19.220 --> 00:03:21.430
No, it's "wayside," not "waste side"!

55
00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:22.770
Who cares which side?!

56
00:03:23.430 --> 00:03:25.890
Guys, just get the hell out of here!

57
00:03:25.890 --> 00:03:27.230
Run!

58
00:03:27.980 --> 00:03:28.980
No way!

59
00:03:28.980 --> 00:03:30.980
We're gonna fight, too!

60
00:03:30.980 --> 00:03:34.150
Running will bring shame
to the Usopp Pi–

61
00:03:44.660 --> 00:03:48.000
Just hurry up and run, you idiots!

62
00:04:00.390 --> 00:04:01.890
– Captain!
– Captain!

63
00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:08.900
That hurt a bit...

64
00:04:08.900 --> 00:04:12.860
What a strange fighting technique...

65
00:04:12.860 --> 00:04:14.280
Can I assume...

66
00:04:14.650 --> 00:04:16.940
that you have devil fruit powers?!

67
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:19.950
Yep! I ate the Gum-Gum Fruit!

68
00:04:21.570 --> 00:04:22.910
I'm a rubber man!

69
00:04:22.910 --> 00:04:24.580
What?! A devil fruit?!

70
00:04:24.580 --> 00:04:25.870
Then he's bad news!

71
00:04:25.870 --> 00:04:27.330
Devil fruits really exist?!

72
00:04:27.330 --> 00:04:28.750
I knew he seemed off!

73
00:04:28.750 --> 00:04:31.130
A rubber man, huh?

74
00:04:31.130 --> 00:04:34.380
So I didn't hallucinate
his arm stretching...

75
00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:36.590
Jango!

76
00:04:36.590 --> 00:04:37.420
Y-Yeah?

77
00:04:37.420 --> 00:04:40.260
The brat is mine.

78
00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:43.050
You take care of Miss Kaya.

79
00:04:43.890 --> 00:04:46.890
As planned, get her to write her will...

80
00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:48.850
then eliminate her!

81
00:04:49.690 --> 00:04:52.100
As for the three little mice...

82
00:04:52.610 --> 00:04:53.610
They're a nuisance!

83
00:04:56.530 --> 00:04:58.190
Consider it done.

84
00:05:02.490 --> 00:05:03.660
Stop.

85
00:05:04.330 --> 00:05:07.500
I'm afraid I can't let you pass.

86
00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:09.830
Buchi!

87
00:05:12.460 --> 00:05:15.960
Cat Astrophe!

88
00:05:16.340 --> 00:05:17.760
Not again!

89
00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:53.960
He's completely different
from before...

90
00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:56.420
Crap!

91
00:05:57.040 --> 00:05:58.710
Dammit...

92
00:06:00.210 --> 00:06:02.380
I can't even lift a finger...

93
00:06:02.380 --> 00:06:05.050
Dammit... Dammit...

94
00:06:05.050 --> 00:06:06.930
Damn...

95
00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:11.520
Usopp Pirates!

96
00:06:12.390 --> 00:06:14.850
– Y-Yes, sir?!
– Y-Yes, sir?!

97
00:06:14.850 --> 00:06:16.400
Listen to your captain!

98
00:06:17.110 --> 00:06:18.520
We're not gonna run!

99
00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:20.320
After what they did to you...

100
00:06:20.320 --> 00:06:22.320
...we'll avenge you!

101
00:06:22.700 --> 00:06:24.570
Protect Kaya!

102
00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:29.830
Listen closely!

103
00:06:29.830 --> 00:06:31.450
I'm giving you...

104
00:06:31.450 --> 00:06:37.080
I'm giving you the most
important part of the mission!

105
00:06:37.080 --> 00:06:40.090
Take Kaya and get away from here!

106
00:06:40.090 --> 00:06:42.010
Don't tell me you can't!

107
00:06:42.010 --> 00:06:46.090
Remember why we
formed our pirate crew!

108
00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:50.100
To become the kind of men who can
protect what's important to us!

109
00:06:52.430 --> 00:06:53.850
Usopp...

110
00:06:58.940 --> 00:07:02.320
That's... a direct order
from your captain...

111
00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:05.280
– Aye, aye, Captain!
– Aye, aye, Captain!

112
00:07:05.280 --> 00:07:06.610
Hurry, Miss Kaya!

113
00:07:06.610 --> 00:07:07.740
This way! This way!

114
00:07:07.070 --> 00:07:07.740
This way!

115
00:07:08.370 --> 00:07:10.700
He definitely has a way with words...

116
00:07:10.700 --> 00:07:12.750
His little speech got them to run...!

117
00:07:12.750 --> 00:07:15.290
These woods are like our backyard!

118
00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:16.170
Okay...

119
00:07:19.340 --> 00:07:20.290
Jango!

120
00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:22.340
Ah, I was mesmerized!

121
00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:25.930
They're fools if they think
they can get awa–

122
00:07:31.140 --> 00:07:32.100
How's that?

123
00:07:32.520 --> 00:07:34.230
You damn bastard!

124
00:07:34.230 --> 00:07:36.640
After them, you moron!

125
00:07:39.230 --> 00:07:40.310
Fine!

126
00:07:42.780 --> 00:07:44.690
An exercise in futility...

127
00:07:45.240 --> 00:07:49.120
If I know anything,
it's how weak Kaya is.

128
00:07:49.120 --> 00:07:52.120
She'll never escape Jango.

129
00:07:52.990 --> 00:07:55.250
If you want to help her,
go right ahead.

130
00:07:56.710 --> 00:08:00.920
Not that you can get up
this hill alive anyway.

131
00:08:06.300 --> 00:08:07.760
Buchi!

132
00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:13.140
You already lost to me once!

133
00:08:13.140 --> 00:08:16.980
Quit wasting my time!

134
00:08:17.390 --> 00:08:19.230
Get lost!

135
00:09:02.690 --> 00:09:05.480
Is that hypnotist still following us?!

136
00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:07.150
Nope, I don't see him!

137
00:09:07.150 --> 00:09:08.940
Let's lose him for good!

138
00:09:08.940 --> 00:09:12.450
As if he can catch us in this forest!

139
00:09:12.990 --> 00:09:14.490
Don't worry, Miss Kaya!

140
00:09:14.490 --> 00:09:16.660
We'll keep you safe!

141
00:09:16.990 --> 00:09:20.000
Yeah! We swear on the name
of the Usopp Pirates!

142
00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:23.330
Thank you...

143
00:09:46.570 --> 00:09:48.070
No sign of them...

144
00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:51.570
Where'd you go, you twerps?!

145
00:09:52.320 --> 00:09:54.700
You can't run forever!

146
00:09:58.040 --> 00:10:03.040
I'll level this entire forest
if that's what it takes!

147
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:04.250
Man...

148
00:10:04.250 --> 00:10:06.500
He's pretty pissed...

149
00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:09.760
He's not just a hypnotist?!

150
00:10:14.220 --> 00:10:16.430
Where did you run off to?

151
00:10:17.510 --> 00:10:18.510
Over there!

152
00:10:26.230 --> 00:10:28.480
Wh-What's that sound?!

153
00:10:28.480 --> 00:10:29.860
Who knows?

154
00:10:29.860 --> 00:10:32.110
Jango is probably
tearing the place up.

155
00:10:32.110 --> 00:10:34.570
Why not go and see for yourself?

156
00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:39.540
Though it may already be too late...

157
00:10:41.540 --> 00:10:43.000
Damn you...!

158
00:10:43.330 --> 00:10:46.460
Don't you even have a shred of pity?!

159
00:10:46.460 --> 00:10:48.590
You lived with her for three years!

160
00:10:48.590 --> 00:10:49.750
None!

161
00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:53.970
Mind you, Kaya is nothing more
than a pawn in my plan.

162
00:10:53.970 --> 00:10:58.430
I'll thank her once she's dead.

163
00:10:59.050 --> 00:11:01.350
Damn you...!

164
00:11:01.350 --> 00:11:03.600
You can't save someone that evil...

165
00:11:03.600 --> 00:11:05.900
I don't plan to save him, though.

166
00:11:07.150 --> 00:11:08.860
Usopp!

167
00:11:10.270 --> 00:11:12.780
Go help them!

168
00:11:13.780 --> 00:11:16.280
We'll take over here!

169
00:11:17.160 --> 00:11:18.570
Leave it to us!

170
00:11:28.580 --> 00:11:32.920
Oh? You can still move?
How impressive.

171
00:11:32.920 --> 00:11:34.420
Shut up...!

172
00:11:34.420 --> 00:11:36.180
I refuse...

173
00:11:36.180 --> 00:11:38.970
to let you get away with this!

174
00:11:39.850 --> 00:11:44.930
You went and betrayed the villagers'—
betrayed Kaya's feelings!

175
00:11:46.100 --> 00:11:50.860
I refuse to let you get away
with any more of your plans!

176
00:11:52.230 --> 00:11:53.320
Usopp!

177
00:11:56.820 --> 00:11:59.030
D-Dammit...

178
00:11:59.030 --> 00:12:03.040
I... can't move...

179
00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:12.590
You really are quite amusing!

180
00:12:12.920 --> 00:12:16.010
Just stay there on the ground.

181
00:12:16.590 --> 00:12:19.840
Though, even if you did
catch up with Jango,

182
00:12:19.840 --> 00:12:22.640
you'd be no match for him anyway.

183
00:12:22.640 --> 00:12:25.140
This is likely the safest option for you!

184
00:12:26.310 --> 00:12:27.980
Even if I am no match...

185
00:12:29.440 --> 00:12:32.690
Even if I am no match for him...

186
00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:35.860
I will protect them!

187
00:12:36.030 --> 00:12:39.320
I'm the captain of the Usopp Pirates,

188
00:12:39.320 --> 00:12:42.410
and I'm going to be
a brave warrior of the sea!

189
00:12:43.030 --> 00:12:50.830
I won't let you lay
a finger on the village!

190
00:12:53.960 --> 00:12:56.170
What's with him?

191
00:12:54.710 --> 00:12:56.170
He's yellin' somethin'!

192
00:12:56.170 --> 00:12:58.630
Check it out, he's cryin'!

193
00:13:11.520 --> 00:13:13.230
What's so funny?!

194
00:13:16.030 --> 00:13:16.980
Luffy!

195
00:13:17.570 --> 00:13:20.950
Me and Usopp are gonna chase
that hypno-freak! That a problem?!

196
00:13:20.950 --> 00:13:22.910
Nope! Hurry!

197
00:13:22.910 --> 00:13:25.160
I-I'm sorry about this...

198
00:13:25.160 --> 00:13:29.410
I'd actually be a lot faster by myself,
but they're inside some woods.

199
00:13:29.410 --> 00:13:32.620
I'm gonna need your directions
to catch up to him.

200
00:13:32.620 --> 00:13:34.630
Hold it, you two.

201
00:13:34.630 --> 00:13:37.880
Who gave you permission
to climb this hill?

202
00:13:38.210 --> 00:13:39.510
I did!

203
00:13:40.840 --> 00:13:42.470
Go! Zoro! Usopp!

204
00:13:44.550 --> 00:13:45.470
And another!

205
00:13:51.940 --> 00:13:56.520
Gum-Gum Spear!

206
00:13:56.520 --> 00:13:58.230
Dammit! He disappeared again!

207
00:14:00.650 --> 00:14:03.860
Oh, well! At least
they made it up the hill!

208
00:14:03.860 --> 00:14:07.490
Before we fight,
I just have one question.

209
00:14:07.490 --> 00:14:11.960
Why is an outsider like you sticking
his nose into the village's business?!

210
00:14:13.170 --> 00:14:16.420
Because there's someone in this
village I don't want dying on me.

211
00:14:17.250 --> 00:14:18.880
How simple.

212
00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:22.260
Are you sure you want that
to be the reason you die?

213
00:14:22.260 --> 00:14:23.970
Yep!

214
00:14:23.970 --> 00:14:25.340
I'm not gonna die, though!

215
00:14:25.840 --> 00:14:27.810
I'll make sure you do!

216
00:14:34.770 --> 00:14:37.560
Gum-Gum Whip!

217
00:14:38.520 --> 00:14:40.280
And Pistol!

218
00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:47.740
What a bore!

219
00:14:47.740 --> 00:14:50.040
Why, you...!

220
00:14:55.870 --> 00:14:59.670
Hey! East! East! I said east!

221
00:14:59.670 --> 00:15:01.920
That's not helpful! Tell me left or right!

222
00:15:01.920 --> 00:15:03.420
Then, turn right!

223
00:15:03.420 --> 00:15:04.630
That's the opposite way!

224
00:15:07.970 --> 00:15:09.560
Miss Kaya!

225
00:15:11.560 --> 00:15:13.310
I'm sorry...

226
00:15:13.310 --> 00:15:15.140
You run on ahead...

227
00:15:15.140 --> 00:15:16.270
What are you saying?!

228
00:15:16.270 --> 00:15:19.400
Our mission is to protect you!

229
00:15:20.730 --> 00:15:22.570
Oh no! She's got a really bad fever!

230
00:15:22.570 --> 00:15:24.650
What?! Hang in there, Miss Kaya!

231
00:15:24.650 --> 00:15:25.780
A doctor...! Get a doctor!

232
00:15:25.780 --> 00:15:28.160
You dummy! Like we
have time for that!

233
00:15:28.160 --> 00:15:29.950
Someone's trying to kill her!

234
00:15:30.450 --> 00:15:32.790
But it's dangerous for
her to keep running!

235
00:15:32.790 --> 00:15:34.080
But...

236
00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:36.460
Where are you, you twerps?!

237
00:15:44.300 --> 00:15:45.760
Thank you...

238
00:15:45.760 --> 00:15:47.430
I'm happy that you helped me...

239
00:15:48.140 --> 00:15:50.760
Just the thought is enough for me...

240
00:15:50.760 --> 00:15:52.510
Run away, all three of you.

241
00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:56.060
Where did you run off to?

242
00:15:58.190 --> 00:16:02.860
If we leave Miss Kaya and run,
we'll probably survive, right?

243
00:16:02.860 --> 00:16:05.190
Yeah, probably.

244
00:16:05.190 --> 00:16:10.530
Our captain always says to run with your
tail between your legs if you're gonna lose...

245
00:16:10.530 --> 00:16:13.200
Our captain is a liar after all!

246
00:16:15.370 --> 00:16:17.960
Even he went and fought!

247
00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:21.040
He tried so hard to protect us!

248
00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:25.840
We won't let Miss Kaya die!

249
00:16:26.220 --> 00:16:29.260
Alright then! Prepare
yourselves, Usopp Pirates!

250
00:16:29.260 --> 00:16:30.090
Yeah!

251
00:16:30.090 --> 00:16:31.550
Let's fight him!

252
00:16:31.550 --> 00:16:32.680
No!

253
00:16:32.680 --> 00:16:34.930
You're still just children!

254
00:16:34.930 --> 00:16:37.520
You mustn't die for my sake!

255
00:16:37.520 --> 00:16:39.140
We're not gonna die.

256
00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:40.520
We're gonna fight to live!

257
00:16:41.730 --> 00:16:43.400
Damn...

258
00:16:43.940 --> 00:16:45.150
He cut my mouth...

259
00:16:45.610 --> 00:16:49.490
That straw hat guy's
insanely strong, and yet...

260
00:16:49.490 --> 00:16:52.410
Th-That's Captain Kuro for ya!

261
00:16:53.160 --> 00:16:54.950
Get 'im!

262
00:16:54.950 --> 00:16:56.580
Hurray for Captain Kuro!

263
00:16:55.660 --> 00:16:56.580
Captain Kuro!

264
00:16:56.580 --> 00:16:59.120
You're awesome, Captain Kuro!

265
00:16:59.120 --> 00:17:02.080
Don't call me by that name!

266
00:17:04.040 --> 00:17:07.050
Do you still not understand?!

267
00:17:07.050 --> 00:17:13.550
The culmination of this plan entirely
rids me of the name "Captain Kuro"!

268
00:17:14.760 --> 00:17:16.850
I'm tired...

269
00:17:17.430 --> 00:17:23.440
Each and every day, devising plans for
men who only care about mayhem...

270
00:17:23.440 --> 00:17:27.940
with government dogs and bounty
hunters nipping at my heels...

271
00:17:27.940 --> 00:17:32.450
I was absolutely sick of it all!

272
00:17:36.200 --> 00:17:38.290
The Marines, huh...?

273
00:17:38.500 --> 00:17:43.380
Kuro of a Thousand Plans
(3 Years Ago)

274
00:17:39.040 --> 00:17:42.670
This is the third time this week...

275
00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.420
That's how it goes.

276
00:17:45.420 --> 00:17:49.010
We're doing stuff that
makes people chase us.

277
00:17:49.010 --> 00:17:51.680
Plus, you've made quite
a name for yourself...

278
00:17:51.680 --> 00:17:53.090
Yes...

279
00:17:53.090 --> 00:17:56.600
That name is what draws them to us.

280
00:17:56.600 --> 00:18:01.140
That's why I'm giving
up being Captain Kuro.

281
00:18:02.850 --> 00:18:05.610
That's a good one.

282
00:18:05.610 --> 00:18:06.980
But it's no use.

283
00:18:06.980 --> 00:18:10.360
The Marines won't
stand down until you're dead.

284
00:18:14.570 --> 00:18:17.030
I am going to die.

285
00:18:18.410 --> 00:18:22.710
It would seem a pirate's
life is not for me...

286
00:18:22.710 --> 00:18:25.830
But... you're the captain!

287
00:18:25.830 --> 00:18:28.590
You can be captain!

288
00:18:28.590 --> 00:18:32.720
I'm sick of this tumultuous lifestyle.

289
00:18:35.300 --> 00:18:39.310
I'm... going to kill myself
for all to see!

290
00:18:40.060 --> 00:18:41.140
Captain Kuro!

291
00:18:41.140 --> 00:18:42.060
Captain...

292
00:18:42.060 --> 00:18:43.020
Captain!

293
00:18:43.020 --> 00:18:44.770
How many vessels?

294
00:18:44.770 --> 00:18:46.400
J-Just one!

295
00:18:46.400 --> 00:18:47.900
What should we do, Captain?

296
00:18:47.900 --> 00:18:50.150
Should we blast 'em back?

297
00:18:50.150 --> 00:18:52.490
Lower a small boat.

298
00:18:52.490 --> 00:18:53.610
Huh?!

299
00:18:53.610 --> 00:18:54.610
Lower it!

300
00:18:58.410 --> 00:19:00.330
First Mate Jango! Captain Kuro...!

301
00:19:00.330 --> 00:19:01.660
Yeah, I know.

302
00:19:01.660 --> 00:19:02.580
"You know"?!

303
00:19:02.580 --> 00:19:05.120
It's too risky to go there by himself!

304
00:19:05.120 --> 00:19:07.880
Don't tell me he's turning himself in?!

305
00:19:22.680 --> 00:19:25.060
Huh?! The cannon fire stopped...

306
00:19:25.600 --> 00:19:27.230
Dock with their ship.

307
00:19:27.230 --> 00:19:28.560
B-But...

308
00:19:28.560 --> 00:19:30.980
Just do as I say, dammit!

309
00:19:30.980 --> 00:19:32.150
Y-Yes, sir!

310
00:19:32.150 --> 00:19:34.240
Hey, get ready to fight!

311
00:19:32.900 --> 00:19:34.240
I see...

312
00:19:34.240 --> 00:19:36.410
Approach the ship!
So that's why...

313
00:19:48.080 --> 00:19:50.420
Th-The Marines...

314
00:19:50.420 --> 00:19:52.670
He wiped them all out!

315
00:19:56.380 --> 00:19:58.300
Now, then...

316
00:19:58.970 --> 00:20:01.810
Let's get this plan underway...!

317
00:20:05.980 --> 00:20:09.060
Hey, now. Pull yourself together.

318
00:20:09.060 --> 00:20:12.230
I was kind enough to leave
you alive, you know...

319
00:20:12.230 --> 00:20:15.240
Sh-Shut up...

320
00:20:15.240 --> 00:20:18.200
I-I'm not gonna beg for my life...

321
00:20:18.990 --> 00:20:22.030
F-Finish me off, damn you...

322
00:20:24.790 --> 00:20:26.750
Looking good there.

323
00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:30.380
If you can howl that much with
a shattered jaw, then that's perfect!

324
00:20:33.340 --> 00:20:39.430
I'm giving you, a nameless,
low-ranking soldier, a treat.

325
00:20:39.430 --> 00:20:42.100
Be grateful and accept it...

326
00:20:42.850 --> 00:20:46.560
The head of Kuro
of a Thousand Plans!

327
00:20:46.980 --> 00:20:49.270
Your name is Captain Kuro.

328
00:20:49.270 --> 00:20:52.190
Your name is Captain Kuro.

329
00:20:52.190 --> 00:20:55.070
This atrocity was your doing.

330
00:20:55.070 --> 00:20:56.190
One...

331
00:20:56.190 --> 00:20:57.440
two...

332
00:20:57.440 --> 00:20:58.530
Jango!

333
00:20:58.950 --> 00:21:01.530
My name is Captain Kuro.

334
00:21:01.530 --> 00:21:04.370
This atrocity was my doing.

335
00:21:04.370 --> 00:21:08.790
And you're the man who
caught Captain Kuro.

336
00:21:08.790 --> 00:21:11.830
Return to base and execute this man.

337
00:21:11.830 --> 00:21:12.750
One...

338
00:21:12.750 --> 00:21:13.840
two...

339
00:21:13.840 --> 00:21:14.800
Jango!

340
00:21:15.880 --> 00:21:19.630
I'm the man who caught Captain Kuro!

341
00:21:19.630 --> 00:21:21.760
You're doing it again, First Mate!

342
00:21:22.220 --> 00:21:23.890
Perfect...

343
00:21:23.890 --> 00:21:32.690
With my replacement gone,
Captain Kuro will disappear from the world.

344
00:21:32.940 --> 00:21:40.400
And today, when my plan succeeds,
my goal will be fully realized...!

345
00:21:40.990 --> 00:21:43.740
I'll have both money
and peace of mind.

346
00:21:44.120 --> 00:21:46.200
Do you understand, boy?

347
00:21:46.200 --> 00:21:51.120
I cannot allow this plan
of three years to fail!

348
00:21:51.460 --> 00:21:55.380
My plan will not be disrupted!

349
00:22:01.550 --> 00:22:04.510
Seems you can do
more than just stretch!

350
00:22:04.510 --> 00:22:05.600
That's right!

351
00:22:05.600 --> 00:22:09.390
I've toughened myself up
to be a pirate!

352
00:22:11.810 --> 00:22:13.560
You're "tired"?!

353
00:22:13.560 --> 00:22:18.110
If you can't handle a reputation on
the seas, you shouldn't be a pirate!

354
00:22:24.780 --> 00:22:27.030
Your ambition...

355
00:22:27.030 --> 00:22:29.910
doesn't even compare to my own!

356
00:22:34.750 --> 00:22:41.610
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

357
00:22:41.810 --> 00:22:48.630
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

358
00:22:48.880 --> 00:22:55.730
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

359
00:22:55.850 --> 00:23:02.990
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

360
00:23:05.690 --> 00:23:08.370
Look where I am

361
00:23:10.600 --> 00:23:16.780
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

362
00:23:17.120 --> 00:23:24.050
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

363
00:23:24.210 --> 00:23:31.130
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

364
00:23:31.260 --> 00:23:38.260
Take me to the place where memories remain

365
00:23:38.360 --> 00:23:44.130
Please don't ever let them fade
